  "text": "Training in the nicotine self-administration procedure. This procedure has been described previously [CITATION_1] . After the period of recovery, rats were trained to intravenously self-administer nicotine (FR1: nicotine, 0.03 mg ⅐ kg Ϫ1 ⅐ infusion Ϫ1 ; TO, 60 s; session duration up to 25 infusions were delivered or 3 h elapsed, no priming injection). Adjustment of nicotine concentration to changes in rat body weight was not needed since rat body weight was kept stable at 250 g (Ϯ10 g). Lever pressing during the TO period was also recorded, although it did not have any consequence. If the animals met the criterion of 25 infusions within the end of the daily session, the FR value was increased to FR2 and then to FR3 with session duration lasting up to 1 h.",
